Linear Model for each country

by.country = matrix(NA,0,7)
for (i in unique(data$Country)) {
test = lm(CM4x~CPO+I(CPO^2),data[data$Country == i,])
a = coef(test)
b = summary(test)$coefficients[,4] #p-values
b2 = summary(test)$coefficients[,2] #SE
d = c(as.numeric(a)[-1],as.numeric(b2)[-1],as.numeric(b)[-1])
d = c(i,d)
by.country = rbind(by.country,d)
}
by.country = as.data.frame(by.country)
names(by.country) = c("Country","CPO","CPO2","SE_CPO","SE_CPO2","p_CPO","p_CPO2")
by.country[,2:7] = apply(by.country[,2:7],2,as.numeric)

by.country$CI95_low_CPO = by.country$CPO-qnorm(.975)*by.country$SE_CPO
by.country$CI95_high_CPO = by.country$CPO+qnorm(.975)*by.country$SE_CPO
by.country$sig_CPO = by.country$p_CPO<.05
by.country$sigbonf_CPO = by.country$p_CPO<.05/nrow(by.country)

by.country$CI95_low_CPO2 = by.country$CPO2-qnorm(.975)*by.country$SE_CPO2
by.country$CI95_high_CPO2 = by.country$CPO2+qnorm(.975)*by.country$SE_CPO2
by.country$sig_CPO2 = by.country$p_CPO2 <.05
by.country$sigbonf_CPO2 = by.country$p_CPO2 <.05/nrow(by.country)

export = by.country[,c(1,2,8,9,10,11,3,12,13,14,15)]
export

Correlation of general with social left-right stance as country-level moderator

# Calculate the new variable (country-wise correlation of lrgen and galtan) and add to the dataset
a = as.character(unique(data$Country))
lr_galtan_cor = c()
data$lr_galtan_cor = NA
for (i in a) {
  dat = data[data$Country==i,]
  re = tryCatch(cor(dat$lrgen,dat$galtan,use="complete.obs"),error=function(x) NA)
  lr_galtan_cor = c(lr_galtan_cor,re)
  # add the correlation to the dataset
  data[data$Country==i,"lr_galtan_cor"] = re
}
names(lr_galtan_cor) = a

Linear Model for each country

by.country = matrix(NA,0,7)
for (i in unique(data$Country)) {
test = lm(CM5x~ZPO+I(ZPO^2),data[data$Country == i,])
a = coef(test)
b = summary(test)$coefficients[,4] #p-values
b2 = summary(test)$coefficients[,2] #SE
d = c(as.numeric(a)[-1],as.numeric(b2)[-1],as.numeric(b)[-1])
d = c(i,d)
by.country = rbind(by.country,d)
}
by.country = as.data.frame(by.country)
names(by.country) = c("Country","ZPO","ZPO2","SE_ZPO","SE_ZPO2","p_ZPO","p_ZPO2")
by.country[,2:7] = apply(by.country[,2:7],2,as.numeric)

by.country$CI95_low_ZPO = by.country$ZPO-qnorm(.975)*by.country$SE_ZPO
by.country$CI95_high_ZPO = by.country$ZPO+qnorm(.975)*by.country$SE_ZPO
by.country$sig_ZPO = by.country$p_ZPO<.05
by.country$sigbonf_ZPO = by.country$p_ZPO<.05/nrow(by.country)

by.country$CI95_low_ZPO2 = by.country$ZPO2-qnorm(.975)*by.country$SE_ZPO2
by.country$CI95_high_ZPO2 = by.country$ZPO2+qnorm(.975)*by.country$SE_ZPO2
by.country$sig_ZPO2 = by.country$p_ZPO2 <.05
by.country$sigbonf_ZPO2 = by.country$p_ZPO2 <.05/nrow(by.country)

export = by.country[,c(1,2,8,9,10,11,3,12,13,14,15)]

Linear Model for each country

by.country = matrix(NA,0,7)
for (i in unique(data$Country)) {
  if (i=="Germany") { # Since Germany is missing education
    test = lm(CM4x~ZPO+I(ZPO^2)+Sex+Age+Winner_state,data[data$Country == i,])
  }
  if (i!="Germany") {
    test = lm(CM4x~ZPO+I(ZPO^2)+Sex+Age+Edu_low+Edu_high+Winner_state,data[data$Country == i,])
  }
  a = coef(test)
  b = summary(test)$coefficients[,4] #p-values
  b2 = summary(test)$coefficients[,2] #SE
  d = c(as.numeric(a)[2:3],as.numeric(b2)[2:3],as.numeric(b)[2:3])
  d = c(i,d)
  by.country = rbind(by.country,d)
}
by.country = as.data.frame(by.country)
names(by.country) = c("Country","ZPO","ZPO2","SE_ZPO","SE_ZPO2","p_ZPO","p_ZPO2")
by.country[,2:7] = apply(by.country[,2:7],2,as.numeric)

by.country$CI95_low_ZPO = by.country$ZPO-qnorm(.975)*by.country$SE_ZPO
by.country$CI95_high_ZPO = by.country$ZPO+qnorm(.975)*by.country$SE_ZPO
by.country$sig_ZPO = by.country$p_ZPO<.05
by.country$sigbonf_ZPO = by.country$p_ZPO<.05/nrow(by.country)

by.country$CI95_low_ZPO2 = by.country$ZPO2-qnorm(.975)*by.country$SE_ZPO2
by.country$CI95_high_ZPO2 = by.country$ZPO2+qnorm(.975)*by.country$SE_ZPO2
by.country$sig_ZPO2 = by.country$p_ZPO2 <.05
by.country$sigbonf_ZPO2 = by.country$p_ZPO2 <.05/nrow(by.country)

export = by.country[,c(1,2,8,9,10,11,3,12,13,14,15)]
export

Linear Model for each country

by.country = matrix(NA,0,7)
for (i in unique(data$Country)) {
test = lm(CM4x~ZPO+I(ZPO^2),data[data$Country == i,])
a = coef(test)
b = summary(test)$coefficients[,4] #p-values
b2 = summary(test)$coefficients[,2] #SE
d = c(as.numeric(a)[-1],as.numeric(b2)[-1],as.numeric(b)[-1])
d = c(i,d)
by.country = rbind(by.country,d)
}
by.country = as.data.frame(by.country)
names(by.country) = c("Country","ZPO","ZPO2","SE_ZPO","SE_ZPO2","p_ZPO","p_ZPO2")
by.country[,2:7] = apply(by.country[,2:7],2,as.numeric)

by.country$CI95_low_ZPO = by.country$ZPO-qnorm(.975)*by.country$SE_ZPO
by.country$CI95_high_ZPO = by.country$ZPO+qnorm(.975)*by.country$SE_ZPO
by.country$sig_ZPO = by.country$p_ZPO<.05
by.country$sigbonf_ZPO = by.country$p_ZPO<.05/nrow(by.country)

by.country$CI95_low_ZPO2 = by.country$ZPO2-qnorm(.975)*by.country$SE_ZPO2
by.country$CI95_high_ZPO2 = by.country$ZPO2+qnorm(.975)*by.country$SE_ZPO2
by.country$sig_ZPO2 = by.country$p_ZPO2 <.05
by.country$sigbonf_ZPO2 = by.country$p_ZPO2 <.05/nrow(by.country)

export = by.country[,c(1,2,8,9,10,11,3,12,13,14,15)]
export
